1
00:00:39,020 --> 00:00:40,590
Sung-jin, it's me.

2
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:44,140
Did I surprise you?

3
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:48,813
I wanted to tell you in person.

4
00:00:50,020 --> 00:00:53,813
But I was afraid
I'd change my mind if I saw you.

5
00:00:54,780 --> 00:00:59,220
I'm leaving now.

6
00:01:00,030 --> 00:01:01,030
For Berlin.

7
00:01:02,970 --> 00:01:04,200
I don’t know…

8
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:07,801
My relationship with you...

9
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:09,833
I'm not sure about it anymore.

10
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:13,039
I don’t understand you.

11
00:01:14,190 --> 00:01:15,740
So I'm really angry, and…

12
00:01:16,890 --> 00:01:19,320
I keep doubting everything,
and it worries me.

13
00:01:22,610 --> 00:01:23,610
And it hurts.

14
00:01:25,630 --> 00:01:26,960
It hurts so much.

15
00:01:30,350 --> 00:01:34,123
I don’t think I’m ready
for marriage right now.

16
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:36,876
So, it's better not to do it.

17
00:01:37,870 --> 00:01:39,198
I’m just weird.

18
00:01:40,590 --> 00:01:42,190
It‘s not your fault.

19
00:01:43,170 --> 00:01:44,170
It's mine.

20
00:01:45,780 --> 00:01:49,320
That’s why I have to leave.

21
00:01:51,530 --> 00:01:53,630
But having you by my side all this time…

22
00:01:57,020 --> 00:01:58,423
It made me truly happy.

23
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:03,810
So, you should be happy too.

24
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:07,920
Goodbye.

25
00:02:21,277 --> 00:02:23,010
<i>Sung-jin, watch this video.</i>

26
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:50,946
HIDDEN FACE

27
00:03:17,990 --> 00:03:21,060
Let's begin at measure 104,
second beat of the first movement.

28
00:03:22,690 --> 00:03:23,710
Here we go.

29
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,960
One, two, three.

30
00:04:15,746 --> 00:04:16,495
Conductor.

31
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:17,539
Yes, Manager.

32
00:04:17,693 --> 00:04:19,426
Wow, look at your face.
You look terrible.

33
00:04:21,290 --> 00:04:22,290
Me?

34
00:04:22,670 --> 00:04:25,906
Anyway, I need to discuss
something with you.

35
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:28,966
It's about the cellist.

36
00:04:29,380 --> 00:04:32,510
We can’t keep rehearsing
with an empty seat, can we?

37
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:37,920
The balance is off.
It doesn’t sound right at all.

38
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:40,880
But everyone’s just exchanging glances,
pretending not to notice.

39
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:46,659
Yes, I know we have to
wait for Su-yeon to return.

40
00:04:46,780 --> 00:04:48,429
But people are starting to talk.

41
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:50,460
I thought I should at least let you know.

42
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:53,710
Yes. I’ll take care of it
as soon as possible.

43
00:04:54,610 --> 00:04:56,116
You understand, right?

44
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:03,060
This is Geisha coffee.

45
00:05:04,030 --> 00:05:05,030
Give it a try.

46
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:06,480
Okay.

47
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:15,320
It’s already been twelve days, hasn’t it?

48
00:05:15,570 --> 00:05:16,840
Yes, almost.

49
00:05:18,310 --> 00:05:20,760
I’m sure she didn’t go to Berlin.

50
00:05:21,220 --> 00:05:23,020
Yes, her cello is still there

51
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,329
and she barely took any clothes.

52
00:05:25,330 --> 00:05:26,590
Don't worry too much.

53
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:28,240
She‘ll be back soon enough.

54
00:05:28,940 --> 00:05:30,020
She was talking nonsense.

55
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:31,880
Like an idiot.

56
00:05:32,460 --> 00:05:35,853
Does she think she can do anything
just because she’s the director’s daughter?

57
00:05:36,470 --> 00:05:37,420
I‘m sorry.

58
00:05:37,421 --> 00:05:39,000
Why are you apologizing?

59
00:05:42,030 --> 00:05:46,170
She‘s probably enjoying room
service at a hotel right now.

60
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,280
It's my fault—
I didn't raise her properly.

61
00:05:49,690 --> 00:05:52,351
I had her when I was immature,
and I spoiled her,

62
00:05:52,376 --> 00:05:53,170
now look at her.

63
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:56,800
Or maybe I raised her well after all…

64
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:59,610
but in the end,
she turned out just like me.

65
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,160
Either way, it‘s my fault.

66
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:03,760
It‘s all on me.

67
00:06:05,350 --> 00:06:06,350
By the way,

68
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:10,120
a cellist is coming for an audition today.

69
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,990
She‘s probably waiting in your office now.

70
00:06:14,330 --> 00:06:15,330
A cellist?

71
00:06:15,410 --> 00:06:15,930
Yes,

72
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:18,599
seems like, she contacted
one of her juniors

73
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,720
to fill in for her.

74
00:06:20,910 --> 00:06:23,970
She does have a sense of
responsibility, after all.

75
00:06:26,610 --> 00:06:29,940
But... shouldn‘t we wait a few more days?

76
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:32,150
Is that so?

77
00:06:32,510 --> 00:06:34,356
Yes. If she suddenly comes back...

78
00:06:34,590 --> 00:06:37,283
...and finds someone else in her place,
she’ll be really disappointed.

79
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:39,750
Honey,

80
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:45,350
I heard you told the manager
that we can’t wait any longer.

81
00:06:46,020 --> 00:06:47,590
That we need a replacement.

82
00:06:48,150 --> 00:06:50,700
You said the orchestra was out of sync.

83
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:53,870
I think you’re right.
After all, you’re the conductor.

84
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:57,710
But you should have told me yourself,

85
00:06:59,070 --> 00:07:00,550
not let me hear it from someone else.

86
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:02,090
But, Director..

87
00:07:02,490 --> 00:07:03,970
- That is...
- Go do the audition.

88
00:07:32,903 --> 00:07:33,740
your profile?

89
00:07:34,540 --> 00:07:35,540
Yes.

90
00:07:40,330 --> 00:07:41,879
I heard you‘re Su-yeon‘s junior,

91
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:43,553
but you didn’t go to
a single school together.

92
00:07:44,190 --> 00:07:47,480
We had the same teacher,
Professor Park Hyun-seong.

93
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:52,049
And when I was preparing
for my entrance exam,

94
00:07:52,050 --> 00:07:53,610
Su-yeon was a teaching
assistant at the school.

95
00:07:54,290 --> 00:07:56,910
She said there’d be an opening here
and suggested I apply.

96
00:07:57,640 --> 00:08:01,200
Did she tell you anything else?

97
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:09,193
The call was out of the blue,
so I was a bit confused.

98
00:08:12,170 --> 00:08:14,270
Am I in the wrong place?

99
00:08:15,093 --> 00:08:16,340
No, that's not it.

100
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:18,810
Let‘s hear you play.

101
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:24,699
Actually, my instrument's
having some issues today.

102
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:29,159
If it's okay, could you listen
to a recording first?

103
00:08:30,650 --> 00:08:31,650
Sure.

104
00:08:56,620 --> 00:09:00,310
Schubert’s "Arpeggione Sonata"

105
00:09:02,790 --> 00:09:05,350
Are you applying just for fun?

106
00:09:06,410 --> 00:09:07,899
What do you mean by that?

107
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:08,900
Well,

108
00:09:09,870 --> 00:09:12,330
how can you apply with such a common piece?

109
00:09:14,410 --> 00:09:18,030
I like Schubert the most.

110
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:21,760
Because his music is the saddest.

111
00:09:22,940 --> 00:09:25,100
The music is so sad that,

112
00:09:25,620 --> 00:09:27,420
when I listen to it,
I don’t even feel sad anymore.

113
00:09:28,110 --> 00:09:29,500
That's why I love him the most.

114
00:09:31,990 --> 00:09:33,609
I'll leave my profile here.

115
00:09:33,610 --> 00:09:35,050
Please throw it in the trash for me.

116
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,919
I‘ll leave the USB too.

117
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:39,559
You can wipe it and
use it for something else.

118
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:40,730
Or just throw it away.

119
00:09:41,340 --> 00:09:43,953
Anyway, it was nice meeting you, Conductor.

120
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:16,760
I like Schubert the most.

121
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:20,480
Because his music is the saddest.

122
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:02,690
What brings you here?

123
00:11:04,980 --> 00:11:06,440
I saw your profile.

124
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:09,360
I didn’t catch you at a bad time,
did I?

125
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:12,860
Well.

126
00:11:13,450 --> 00:11:15,280
I was too rude earlier today.

127
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:17,870
I was upset about something else,

128
00:11:17,990 --> 00:11:20,080
and I think I took it out on you.

129
00:11:21,460 --> 00:11:22,670
I came here to apologize.

130
00:11:23,420 --> 00:11:24,420
I‘m sorry.

131
00:11:25,090 --> 00:11:26,090
Yes.

132
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:27,300
I understand.

133
00:11:27,340 --> 00:11:28,710
And your performance,

134
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:30,130
I really liked it too.

135
00:11:37,140 --> 00:11:39,140
Please join our orchestra.

136
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:41,350
Really?

137
00:11:43,126 --> 00:11:44,133
Well,

138
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:45,560
for me,

139
00:11:46,230 --> 00:11:47,526
this is definitely great news.

140
00:11:59,783 --> 00:12:00,950
Oh, it’s Schubert.

141
00:12:01,250 --> 00:12:02,370
Yes, that's right.

142
00:12:02,830 --> 00:12:03,870
It's Schubert.

143
00:12:04,540 --> 00:12:06,000
It’s the piece we’re performing.

144
00:12:10,670 --> 00:12:12,220
I think that’s it.

145
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:13,710
Please practice and come over.

146
00:12:17,260 --> 00:12:18,350
Ah, actually,

147
00:12:18,970 --> 00:12:20,930
Schubert is my favorite too.

148
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:22,140
And the reason…

149
00:12:23,310 --> 00:12:24,440
It’s the same as yours.

150
00:13:22,763 --> 00:13:24,500
Ah, well...

151
00:13:25,750 --> 00:13:26,570
For now

152
00:13:26,750 --> 00:13:29,080
Her instrument is too cheap.

153
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:30,630
You can hear it right away.

154
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:32,130
It doesn't blend at all.

155
00:13:32,460 --> 00:13:33,760
Right, Director?

156
00:13:35,220 --> 00:13:37,180
Well, she’s practiced quite a bit,

157
00:13:37,380 --> 00:13:39,306
but she’s still pretty unpolished.

158
00:13:40,010 --> 00:13:42,850
We really needed Su-yeon
for this practice.

159
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:45,890
See?

160
00:13:46,626 --> 00:13:48,260
We should’ve waited for Su-yeon.

161
00:13:49,020 --> 00:13:52,110
What do you think of her
performance today?

162
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:57,610
Well, it’s just her first time.

163
00:13:57,950 --> 00:13:59,780
We need to watch her play more.

164
00:14:00,820 --> 00:14:01,870
But still...

165
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:04,080
there should be some
kind of intuition, right?

166
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:06,040
Or perhaps, a feeling?

167
00:14:10,210 --> 00:14:12,500
You could say she’s the
hardworking type.

168
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:16,460
Given her practice time, her performance
exceeded my expectations.

169
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:19,430
Well, her attitude is also very good.

170
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:23,720
Well then,

171
00:14:24,470 --> 00:14:27,480
as a conductor,
if you have no complaints,

172
00:14:28,350 --> 00:14:29,520
it’s all good.

173
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,900
But still,

174
00:14:33,083 --> 00:14:35,616
I guess you’re satisfied with her
'only as a substitute,' right?

175
00:14:36,110 --> 00:14:37,216
That's what you meant, right?

176
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,240
Isn‘t it?

177
00:14:38,583 --> 00:14:39,231
Right?

178
00:14:39,256 --> 00:14:42,136
The conductor himself said he's satisfied.
So why are you more concerned than him?

179
00:14:42,410 --> 00:14:44,069
He literally said she's hardworking
and has a great attitude,

180
00:14:44,094 --> 00:14:45,502
and he's satisfied! Didn't he?

181
00:14:47,229 --> 00:14:48,736
Looks like she doesn’t even
need to come back.

182
00:14:48,910 --> 00:14:49,910
That crazy bitch.

183
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:59,130
This happens a lot,

184
00:14:59,616 --> 00:15:01,509
and after a few tries,
I can usually get it to work.

185
00:15:01,534 --> 00:15:03,180
But this time,
it won’t start at all.

186
00:15:05,010 --> 00:15:06,010
Okay.

187
00:15:07,350 --> 00:15:08,480
This is Goyang City.

188
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:11,480
What?

189
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,230
Can’t you please come quickly?

190
00:15:19,570 --> 00:15:20,830
Something wrong with your car?

191
00:15:20,950 --> 00:15:22,443
It broke down.

192
00:15:26,450 --> 00:15:27,563
Are you off work?

193
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:29,950
Yes.

194
00:15:48,770 --> 00:15:50,640
The cello looks really small.

195
00:15:52,140 --> 00:15:54,100
It seemed so big in the backseat of my car.

196
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:57,980
At least it fit.

197
00:15:58,650 --> 00:16:00,150
I doubted it would fit.

198
00:16:00,740 --> 00:16:01,950
When did you see it?

199
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:06,320
That day...

200
00:16:06,530 --> 00:16:07,756
The day you came for the interview.

201
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:09,490
I happened to see it through the window.

202
00:16:10,410 --> 00:16:11,410
Really?

203
00:16:12,540 --> 00:16:13,750
It‘s a bit embarrassing.

204
00:16:15,830 --> 00:16:16,830
Over there...

205
00:16:18,250 --> 00:16:19,603
Shall we grab dinner?

206
00:16:22,970 --> 00:16:24,220
Yeah, sounds good!

207
00:16:31,180 --> 00:16:34,140
By the way, I like grilling meat too.

208
00:16:34,230 --> 00:16:36,310
I never even touched the tongs before.

209
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:38,480
I have a bit of a complex.

210
00:16:38,730 --> 00:16:39,820
A complex?

211
00:16:40,436 --> 00:16:41,996
I‘m the son of a diner owner.

212
00:16:43,740 --> 00:16:45,410
If I grill too well,

213
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:49,146
people will say, "No wonder
he's the son of a diner owner."

214
00:17:03,130 --> 00:17:04,220
It's raining.

215
00:17:05,470 --> 00:17:07,800
Oh no, we don't have an umbrella.

216
00:17:14,349 --> 00:17:16,029
But it's nice that it's raining.

217
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:24,490
By the way,

218
00:17:24,990 --> 00:17:28,990
I heard from other members that
something happened between you two.

219
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,200
Did you have a fight?

220
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:33,461
- Did she leave...
- Can we not talk about this?

221
00:17:33,830 --> 00:17:35,210
I don‘t really want to discuss it.

222
00:17:42,340 --> 00:17:44,760
Oh, right, I have a complex too.

223
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:46,920
What is it?

224
00:17:47,970 --> 00:17:49,313
I‘m an orphan.

225
00:17:50,390 --> 00:17:51,810
When I was in high school,

226
00:17:51,930 --> 00:17:53,640
my parents had an accident.

227
00:17:54,560 --> 00:17:55,600
A car accident.

228
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:57,730
They passed away together.

229
00:17:58,980 --> 00:18:00,980
My mom and dad,

230
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:02,440
both of them.

231
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:05,700
So I have an orphan complex.

232
00:18:07,860 --> 00:18:08,860
Cheers.

233
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:21,373
Thank you.

234
00:18:21,572 --> 00:18:22,332
Go on.

235
00:18:22,826 --> 00:18:23,626
It's cold.

236
00:18:24,473 --> 00:18:25,326
Yes, take care.

237
00:18:25,353 --> 00:18:26,380
Yeah.

238
00:18:26,426 --> 00:18:27,459
Yeah, go on.

239
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:29,880
Go.

240
00:18:31,890 --> 00:18:34,140
Should I sit in the back?

241
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,879
I'm smaller and slimmer, after all.

242
00:18:38,810 --> 00:18:40,810
Ah, it's not needed.

243
00:18:42,770 --> 00:18:45,150
Once the driver arrives,

244
00:18:45,230 --> 00:18:47,610
we'll take you home first,

245
00:18:48,780 --> 00:18:50,950
and take the cello down.

246
00:18:50,990 --> 00:18:54,555
and then only it makes sense
for me to sit in the front, right?

247
00:18:54,580 --> 00:18:57,290
You‘ve said that five times already.

248
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:00,160
Really?

249
00:19:09,670 --> 00:19:11,030
Because it's raining,

250
00:19:11,470 --> 00:19:13,563
the alcohol went down so smoothly.

251
00:19:24,690 --> 00:19:26,363
Ah, I want to drink more.

252
00:19:27,043 --> 00:19:28,470
They must have closed it by now, right?

253
00:19:45,670 --> 00:19:47,460
Mi-joo.

254
00:19:48,670 --> 00:19:49,670
Yes?

255
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:53,090
Shall we have one more drink?

256
00:19:54,510 --> 00:19:55,510
From where?

257
00:19:59,020 --> 00:20:00,340
Do you want to go to my place?

258
00:20:22,540 --> 00:20:25,173
Actually, I don't know anything about wine.

259
00:20:25,830 --> 00:20:27,040
This must be a good wine.

260
00:20:28,290 --> 00:20:29,850
Honestly, I have no idea either.

261
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,720
You don‘t have to agree with me.

262
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:34,200
You sure know a lot about it.

263
00:20:34,260 --> 00:20:36,220
I really don‘t. I just drink it like this.

264
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:38,640
And I...

265
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:44,810
People who go into detail
about wine or coffee...

266
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,560
I just can’t stand them.

267
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:50,900
What?

268
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:53,570
Like saying it smells like August earth...

269
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:57,280
Or that it has absorbed the sun of May...

270
00:20:57,613 --> 00:20:58,615
Stuff like that,

271
00:20:58,733 --> 00:20:59,746
ridiculous.

272
00:21:00,990 --> 00:21:01,990
Then,

273
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:06,250
let’s toast as people who
don’t really understand it.

274
00:21:31,090 --> 00:21:33,070
This house is really nice.

275
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,380
I‘m completely drunk.

276
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:53,250
I knew it, wine is poison for me.

277
00:21:53,980 --> 00:21:56,510
I'm all dizzy, even after washing my face.

278
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:06,293
Drunk & Soaked in the rain...

279
00:22:06,525 --> 00:22:08,020
It's a complete mess.

280
00:22:20,130 --> 00:22:21,130
Don‘t do this.

281
00:22:29,170 --> 00:22:30,380
Not in this room...

282
00:22:31,290 --> 00:22:33,250
We can’t do this here.

283
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:35,170
This feels wrong.

284
00:22:36,530 --> 00:22:38,590
How am I supposed to face her after this?

285
00:23:00,150 --> 00:23:01,150
Wait a moment.

286
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:31,770
I did that because I like you.

287
00:24:14,110 --> 00:24:15,860
Why did you take everything off?

288
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:31,680
Apparently, that’s civet cat poop.
They eat coffee beans and poop them out.

289
00:25:33,610 --> 00:25:34,720
Cool, right?

290
00:25:35,620 --> 00:25:36,350
Yeah.

291
00:25:36,351 --> 00:25:38,309
It’s all about how you present it.

292
00:25:38,310 --> 00:25:41,456
Even poop looks fancy when they
present it well and sell it for a fortune.

293
00:25:41,716 --> 00:25:43,296
Well, it looks pretty fancy,
doesn’t it?

294
00:25:43,576 --> 00:25:45,440
The actual content doesn’t really matter.

295
00:25:46,210 --> 00:25:48,160
It’s all about how people see it.

296
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:50,280
Perception is everything.

297
00:25:53,210 --> 00:25:56,870
That’s why people need to
present themselves well too.

298
00:25:59,250 --> 00:26:01,617
People are all about how they
present themselves too, right?

299
00:26:04,350 --> 00:26:05,380
By the way,

300
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:08,970
speaking of Su-yeon,

301
00:26:09,956 --> 00:26:11,376
don’t you think she’s a bit strange?

302
00:26:12,310 --> 00:26:16,270
I thought she was acting this way
because she‘s about to get married.

303
00:26:16,980 --> 00:26:18,190
But this feels kinda strange.

304
00:26:19,100 --> 00:26:20,730
Do you know what‘s the strangest thing?

305
00:26:23,500 --> 00:26:24,586
She‘s not using my card.

306
00:26:25,950 --> 00:26:27,180
Su-yeon is the kind of person

307
00:26:27,206 --> 00:26:29,820
who would still use my card
even if I died the day before.

308
00:26:30,820 --> 00:26:32,330
But she hasn‘t been using it at all.

309
00:26:32,833 --> 00:26:33,846
That’s so strange.

310
00:26:33,871 --> 00:26:37,960
What if that’s just her way of
showing how angry she really is?

311
00:26:38,630 --> 00:26:39,630
I mean…

312
00:26:40,360 --> 00:26:44,890
Maybe she just wants to make it
look like she disappeared completely.

313
00:26:45,780 --> 00:26:47,100
That‘s what it seems like, right?

314
00:26:48,510 --> 00:26:50,260
I‘m starting to worry about her.

315
00:26:50,690 --> 00:26:52,890
She’s not usually this determined.

316
00:26:53,990 --> 00:26:54,990
Yeah.

317
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:04,860
It rained a lot yesterday.

318
00:27:05,630 --> 00:27:07,320
That wasn‘t my fault.

319
00:27:08,290 --> 00:27:11,610
But everything else was.

320
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:13,909
Drinking too much,

321
00:27:13,910 --> 00:27:15,200
going to your place…

322
00:27:15,790 --> 00:27:17,500
Especially going into the bedroom.

323
00:27:18,150 --> 00:27:20,210
To make sure I don’t mess up again…

324
00:27:20,790 --> 00:27:23,129
I won’t reply to your messages anymore.

325
00:27:23,130 --> 00:27:24,500
I hope you’ll understand me.

326
00:28:01,870 --> 00:28:03,330
[Cello Kim Mi-joo]

327
00:28:07,703 --> 00:28:08,753
<i>Hello?</i>

328
00:28:12,380 --> 00:28:13,380
<i>Hello?</i>

329
00:29:50,339 --> 00:29:52,352
You think I’m crazy, don’t you?

330
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,293
I wasn‘t supposed to come here.

331
00:29:57,470 --> 00:29:58,790
But I‘ve come here twice already.

332
00:30:07,830 --> 00:30:11,496
You played the piano
and made me come here.

333
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:18,730
Twice already...

334
00:30:19,260 --> 00:30:20,890
That, too, in her bedroom..

335
00:31:10,130 --> 00:31:11,130
What‘s wrong?

336
00:31:12,460 --> 00:31:14,879
Suddenly, only hot water
is coming out of the shower.

337
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:16,200
It‘s okay.

338
00:31:16,225 --> 00:31:17,920
- Hot water? Why?
- It‘s really fine.

339
00:31:17,921 --> 00:31:19,761
- It wasn’t hot at all.
- Are you alright?

340
00:31:19,970 --> 00:31:20,970
You should go out.

341
00:31:27,380 --> 00:31:31,170
[Three months ago]

342
00:31:33,790 --> 00:31:35,743
What the heck? So annoying.

343
00:31:37,010 --> 00:31:39,170
I was planning to hug you at the gate.

344
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,563
What’s more urgent than me?

345
00:31:43,130 --> 00:31:44,170
I don‘t know.

346
00:31:46,420 --> 00:31:49,089
Sung-jin, Mom said she couldn‘t come.

347
00:31:49,090 --> 00:31:50,296
So she sent someone.

348
00:31:51,946 --> 00:31:54,169
I‘ll ask him to come here.

349
00:31:54,170 --> 00:31:55,749
We‘ve got way too much luggage.

350
00:31:55,750 --> 00:31:56,960
It’s okay, no worries.

351
00:31:57,260 --> 00:32:00,119
Sung-jin, let‘s grab a hot Americano.

352
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:01,700
I smelled it,
and now I want some too.

353
00:32:02,330 --> 00:32:03,330
Do we have to?

354
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:09,130
Hey, it's me.

355
00:32:10,170 --> 00:32:12,006
Please come to Gate 4.

356
00:32:13,179 --> 00:32:14,152
Okay.

357
00:32:18,355 --> 00:32:19,439
Wow!

358
00:32:20,540 --> 00:32:22,790
I didn‘t expect you to come to the airport.

359
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:27,193
I was just bored,

360
00:32:28,540 --> 00:32:29,753
so I came to give you the keys.

361
00:32:30,210 --> 00:32:31,326
And also to welcome you?

362
00:32:31,460 --> 00:32:32,820
Forget the welcome.

363
00:32:33,790 --> 00:32:35,733
Didn‘t we agree to leave
the keys at the door?

364
00:32:37,630 --> 00:32:38,800
Here you go.

365
00:32:44,040 --> 00:32:45,486
About the renovation,

366
00:32:47,260 --> 00:32:48,695
even though it‘s done,

367
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:50,753
- I‘m not sure if it suits your taste.
- Hey.

368
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:54,586
I kept watching everything on video
during the renovation

369
00:32:55,170 --> 00:32:58,113
And you proceeded
only when I said 'Okay.'

370
00:32:58,420 --> 00:33:00,696
So, of course, it should
suit my taste, right?

371
00:33:01,290 --> 00:33:02,670
Why say unnecessary things?

372
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:06,959
Got it.

373
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:11,373
The thing that does not suit my taste is...

374
00:33:12,710 --> 00:33:14,750
you showing up at the airport like this.

375
00:33:15,053 --> 00:33:16,613
Don't you think this is a bit too much?

376
00:33:17,340 --> 00:33:18,560
That’s right too.

377
00:33:19,050 --> 00:33:21,730
I’m grateful, but being grateful
is still one thing...

378
00:33:22,920 --> 00:33:24,480
What’s not right is just not right.

379
00:33:25,370 --> 00:33:26,296
Got it?

380
00:33:28,010 --> 00:33:29,010
Yes.

381
00:33:37,215 --> 00:33:38,181
Let‘s go.

382
00:34:07,296 --> 00:34:08,178
Do you like it?

383
00:34:08,203 --> 00:34:09,429
Wow, this is so huge!

384
00:34:10,500 --> 00:34:12,710
When I used to come here as a student,

385
00:34:12,920 --> 00:34:15,725
I would always wonder why my
teacher lived in such a creepy house.

386
00:34:15,750 --> 00:34:17,896
But as I got older,
I kept thinking about it again.

387
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:20,246
It looks nice now, since it's been
completely redone, right?

388
00:34:21,170 --> 00:34:22,170
Do you like it?

389
00:34:22,630 --> 00:34:24,073
Of course, I like it.

390
00:34:25,920 --> 00:34:28,010
You can play music as loud as you want,

391
00:34:28,571 --> 00:34:30,451
and there's also this beautiful garden.

392
00:34:34,630 --> 00:34:36,410
Living in a house like this
was my dream,

393
00:34:37,170 --> 00:34:38,936
but I got it without even trying.

394
00:34:42,460 --> 00:34:44,910
Why?
Don't you like it?

395
00:34:46,130 --> 00:34:49,413
I said I like it,
but it's a bit overwhelming...

396
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:51,886
Do I even deserve to live here?

397
00:34:59,230 --> 00:35:00,643
You have to get used to it.

398
00:35:02,670 --> 00:35:03,685
What?

399
00:35:03,710 --> 00:35:04,823
To everything.

400
00:35:05,783 --> 00:35:07,976
Everything you've never
experienced before, Sung-jin.

401
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:10,942
Do you know why?

402
00:35:12,289 --> 00:35:13,713
Because you, Sung-jin...

403
00:35:14,336 --> 00:35:15,880
You're a maestro.

404
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:18,853
Maestro

405
00:35:19,413 --> 00:35:21,926
For a maestro,
everything is a given.

406
00:35:26,035 --> 00:35:29,195
For my mom, getting us a house
like this isn’t even a big deal.

407
00:35:29,220 --> 00:35:30,341
Don‘t feel burdened.

408
00:35:30,939 --> 00:35:32,286
It’s not a burden, but…

409
00:35:34,025 --> 00:35:35,285
I’m just not used to it.

410
00:35:38,420 --> 00:35:41,092
Everything comes naturally
for you, Sung-jin.

411
00:35:41,250 --> 00:35:43,512
Got it, my Maestro?

412
00:35:47,440 --> 00:35:48,855
<i>There's a place I visited recently…</i>

413
00:35:48,880 --> 00:35:50,026
<i>Did you like it?</i>

414
00:35:50,730 --> 00:35:54,029
<i>Yeah, the place was great. The back is
all jungle, and the front is the ocean.</i>

415
00:35:54,336 --> 00:35:55,823
<i>- Really?
- Yeah.</i>

416
00:35:57,710 --> 00:35:59,323
Amazing!

417
00:35:59,550 --> 00:36:01,683
A jungle at the back,
and the ocean in the front?

418
00:36:02,936 --> 00:36:04,300
Sung-jin, look at this!

419
00:36:04,683 --> 00:36:06,169
Isn't it amazing?

420
00:36:06,170 --> 00:36:07,435
Don't look at her bikini.

421
00:36:07,460 --> 00:36:08,643
Ah, that...

422
00:36:10,090 --> 00:36:12,330
Wow, this is insane!

423
00:36:13,276 --> 00:36:16,476
30 million won for 5 nights
is a bit expensive...

424
00:36:16,501 --> 00:36:17,525
But it's worth it.

425
00:36:17,550 --> 00:36:18,525
Good, right?

426
00:36:18,550 --> 00:36:21,060
You're having the ceremony
right after the performance, right?

427
00:36:21,070 --> 00:36:21,850
Yes.

428
00:36:22,236 --> 00:36:25,503
But since it’s peak season then, the
price will probably go up a little more.

429
00:36:25,736 --> 00:36:26,643
Well, it doesn’t matter.

430
00:37:23,555 --> 00:37:24,642
Oh wow, look at you!

431
00:37:26,722 --> 00:37:27,709
Darling.

432
00:37:28,902 --> 00:37:30,336
I can smoke here, right?

433
00:37:30,635 --> 00:37:31,729
Yes, of course.

434
00:37:32,435 --> 00:37:34,541
But why wash the dishes?

435
00:37:34,835 --> 00:37:36,375
There aren't enough cups.

436
00:37:40,615 --> 00:37:41,695
It really suits you.

437
00:37:44,308 --> 00:37:48,035
By the way, did your mom say
anything after meeting?

438
00:37:51,261 --> 00:37:52,527
Well, she really liked you.

439
00:37:53,020 --> 00:37:54,641
She said you were very elegant.

440
00:37:55,761 --> 00:37:57,847
and she's very happy that
I'm marrying into a good family.

441
00:38:00,954 --> 00:38:01,974
But,

442
00:38:02,781 --> 00:38:04,334
after the family meeting,

443
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:06,254
I started seeing you
in a new light.

444
00:38:08,220 --> 00:38:10,300
You really are a remarkable person.

445
00:38:11,130 --> 00:38:12,985
You have incredible willpower

446
00:38:13,010 --> 00:38:14,754
and a strong sense of self.

447
00:38:15,760 --> 00:38:19,733
I could sense just how much effort
you put into your image.

448
00:38:20,366 --> 00:38:21,726
Why all of a sudden...?

449
00:38:22,130 --> 00:38:24,932
It’s nothing, just how I felt.

450
00:38:26,479 --> 00:38:28,252
Wow, as they used to say
in the old days,

451
00:38:29,099 --> 00:38:30,526
you're really a self-made man.

452
00:38:34,760 --> 00:38:37,973
I've come to like you even more.

453
00:38:51,253 --> 00:38:53,260
I was really worried about
the housewarming party.

454
00:38:54,090 --> 00:38:57,460
But in the end, it was both
fulfilling and grand.

455
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:58,640
Right?

456
00:39:01,033 --> 00:39:02,486
How about that place we saw earlier?

457
00:39:04,179 --> 00:39:05,186
That place?

458
00:39:06,600 --> 00:39:08,162
The resort we saw in the pictures.

459
00:39:08,310 --> 00:39:09,462
I really liked it.

460
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:11,840
Didn't we agree that you'd
handle those things yourself?

461
00:39:16,366 --> 00:39:18,626
Darling, You don’t seem
to be in a good mood.

462
00:39:23,213 --> 00:39:24,406
By any chance,

463
00:39:25,300 --> 00:39:27,253
Is it because of what they said earlier?

464
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:28,735
What did they say?

465
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:31,713
They said it was unexpected
when I told them I seduced you.

466
00:39:32,620 --> 00:39:35,728
Like they couldn’t even imagine
it happening the other way around.

467
00:39:35,753 --> 00:39:37,506
That never crossed my mind.

468
00:39:38,866 --> 00:39:39,899
Is that so?

469
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:41,840
Okay.

470
00:39:42,580 --> 00:39:46,613
Then, that resort it is, right?

471
00:39:47,013 --> 00:39:48,526
Five nights, 30 million won?

472
00:39:49,886 --> 00:39:51,193
You think that’s expensive?

473
00:39:52,363 --> 00:39:55,000
Why stress?
Mom’s paying anyway.

474
00:39:55,380 --> 00:39:58,050
Also, darling,

475
00:39:58,630 --> 00:40:02,043
I absolutely hate that attitude.

476
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:05,160
The one where you talk like
you're mocking me.

477
00:40:05,690 --> 00:40:07,540
I like everything the best,

478
00:40:08,100 --> 00:40:11,930
which is the most luxurious and cozy.

479
00:40:13,070 --> 00:40:16,383
But when you criticize and
mock me for things like that,

480
00:40:17,460 --> 00:40:18,703
that's what I hate the most.

481
00:40:20,002 --> 00:40:23,356
Let's fix that, okay?

482
00:40:24,922 --> 00:40:25,822
Okay.

483
00:40:26,982 --> 00:40:27,915
Got it.

484
00:40:27,940 --> 00:40:29,580
You go ahead and sleep.

485
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:33,476
Kiss me before you go.

486
00:41:24,410 --> 00:41:25,410
 Yeah

487
00:41:28,370 --> 00:41:29,345
How was it?

488
00:41:29,370 --> 00:41:30,131
What?

489
00:41:30,156 --> 00:41:31,329
I'm getting better, right?

490
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:35,309
I feel like you're much more
at ease now than before.

491
00:41:37,016 --> 00:41:40,209
If you're going to compliment me,
do it properly, director.

492
00:41:40,390 --> 00:41:41,622
Let‘s skip that.

493
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:43,573
Now, look at this.

494
00:41:43,598 --> 00:41:44,821
<i>Performance Plan</i>

495
00:41:44,846 --> 00:41:46,826
The planning
department gave it to me.

496
00:41:46,851 --> 00:41:48,340
We need to make
a decision together.

497
00:41:50,752 --> 00:41:53,500
They insist on opening
with "Unfinished Symphony."

498
00:41:53,510 --> 00:41:54,600
So, let's go with that.

499
00:41:54,830 --> 00:41:56,905
After that, it should be more lyrical.

500
00:41:57,160 --> 00:42:00,187
This was the performance program
arranged for the Vienna event.

501
00:42:00,212 --> 00:42:01,630
I think it's quite good.

502
00:42:01,640 --> 00:42:03,920
Of course, it was very successful.

503
00:42:03,945 --> 00:42:06,155
This should go the same way,
even the opening piece.

504
00:42:06,179 --> 00:42:07,105
- Of course!

505
00:42:13,780 --> 00:42:14,710
By the way,

506
00:42:15,343 --> 00:42:19,343
What were you talking about
with that violinist earlier?

507
00:42:20,383 --> 00:42:21,383
The violinist?

508
00:42:21,940 --> 00:42:24,286
Wasn't it In-jeong on stage earlier today?

509
00:42:24,660 --> 00:42:27,073
It looked like you two were having
a really fun conversation.

510
00:42:28,653 --> 00:42:29,686
Did we?

511
00:42:32,193 --> 00:42:36,153
When she suddenly reached out her hand,
you gazed at it with such care.

512
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:42,826
She said she's worried
because her nails are weak.

513
00:42:42,850 --> 00:42:44,253
And that they keep breaking.

514
00:42:54,416 --> 00:42:55,516
What's the matter?

515
00:42:59,656 --> 00:43:00,690
What do you mean?

516
00:43:01,903 --> 00:43:04,930
Why do you seem different
since coming to Seoul?

517
00:43:06,040 --> 00:43:07,170
What are you talking about?

518
00:43:07,890 --> 00:43:11,543
You're kind to the violinist,
and to everyone else too.

519
00:43:13,089 --> 00:43:15,236
But why are you so cold to me?

520
00:43:17,609 --> 00:43:20,536
Everything I do, you either
mock it or just don’t care.

521
00:43:22,120 --> 00:43:23,220
Why is that?

522
00:43:39,837 --> 00:43:41,223
Should I say something too?

523
00:43:42,020 --> 00:43:43,020
What is it?

524
00:43:43,717 --> 00:43:45,683
Why are you making me feel
so embarrassed?

525
00:43:46,360 --> 00:43:48,303
Who? Me?

526
00:43:48,583 --> 00:43:51,753
Did the two of you really have to have
a private meeting in front of everyone?

527
00:43:53,710 --> 00:43:56,468
Do you really have to let everyone
know the conductor is just a puppet?

528
00:43:56,493 --> 00:43:58,228
No, that's not it.

529
00:43:58,253 --> 00:44:01,795
Mom wanted to discuss it with me first
and then decide with you.

530
00:44:01,826 --> 00:44:03,206
So that first discussion...

531
00:44:04,486 --> 00:44:07,350
did it really have to be there
with all the members watching?

532
00:44:10,810 --> 00:44:11,810
Is it really that

533
00:44:12,720 --> 00:44:14,080
embarrassing to you?

534
00:44:14,610 --> 00:44:17,170
Should I be proud to
be treated like a puppet?

535
00:44:55,360 --> 00:44:56,906
You‘re wearing a bracelet today.

536
00:44:57,850 --> 00:45:02,506
I was too much at the airport last time.

537
00:45:03,586 --> 00:45:04,820
I want to apologize.

538
00:45:08,080 --> 00:45:10,393
Well, that’s understandable.

539
00:45:17,200 --> 00:45:19,500
By the way, why didn‘t you
come to the housewarming party?

540
00:45:20,070 --> 00:45:21,390
You didn‘t invite me.

541
00:45:21,790 --> 00:45:24,210
Oh, I must be crazy.
I thought I invited you.

542
00:45:26,930 --> 00:45:28,150
That's exactly your style.

543
00:45:32,462 --> 00:45:34,350
Ah, you’re always cool.

544
00:45:34,670 --> 00:45:35,736
I really like it.

545
00:45:37,442 --> 00:45:40,236
I‘m really going crazy because of Sung-jin.

546
00:45:40,609 --> 00:45:43,502
He’s good-looking and
promising as a conductor,

547
00:45:44,366 --> 00:45:47,046
Although his family is not well-off,
it doesn‘t matter.

548
00:45:48,590 --> 00:45:49,773
But one thing bothers me.

549
00:45:50,690 --> 00:45:51,690
What is it?

550
00:45:52,350 --> 00:45:53,570
He doesn‘t seem to like me.

551
00:45:56,010 --> 00:45:58,836
But you like him?

552
00:45:59,720 --> 00:46:00,743
Are you out of your mind?

553
00:46:01,820 --> 00:46:03,990
But not liking me is not acceptable.

554
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:06,160
Even if I don't like him,
he still has to like me.

555
00:46:06,170 --> 00:46:07,400
That's only natural.

556
00:46:09,009 --> 00:46:10,570
How is that natural?

557
00:46:11,100 --> 00:46:12,100
It is.

558
00:46:16,663 --> 00:46:21,490
So, are you giving me advice right now?

559
00:46:30,007 --> 00:46:31,020
Mi-joo.

560
00:46:32,046 --> 00:46:38,600
Do you remember the day I
kissed you for the first time?

561
00:46:44,500 --> 00:46:45,500
When was it?

562
00:46:46,513 --> 00:46:51,326
In the warehouse behind
the teacher‘s house.

563
00:46:52,920 --> 00:46:58,120
Since that day,
I haven‘t liked anyone else but you.

564
00:47:02,240 --> 00:47:03,440
You feel the same, right?

565
00:47:09,993 --> 00:47:14,230
Even though I‘m betraying you now...

566
00:47:14,653 --> 00:47:16,133
Yes, I'm betraying you.

567
00:47:18,079 --> 00:47:20,473
But I will never betray our memories.

568
00:47:23,899 --> 00:47:25,592
I hope you understand that.

569
00:47:28,260 --> 00:47:29,499
I understand.

570
00:47:32,010 --> 00:47:33,292
Okay.

571
00:47:35,420 --> 00:47:38,760
Did you go to the warehouse
when you were fixing it?

572
00:47:41,070 --> 00:47:42,070
Yes.

573
00:47:42,660 --> 00:47:44,940
That means the key is with you.

574
00:47:59,025 --> 00:48:00,785
So, you decorated it like this.

575
00:48:01,390 --> 00:48:02,545
It looks really good.

576
00:48:03,511 --> 00:48:05,285
What’s the point
if only the house is nice?

577
00:48:05,573 --> 00:48:07,298
The relationship has to be too.

578
00:48:08,591 --> 00:48:09,658
Come with me.

579
00:48:14,580 --> 00:48:15,912
You brought the key, right?

580
00:48:27,666 --> 00:48:29,573
Do we really have to go this far?

581
00:48:31,466 --> 00:48:32,900
I’m really angry, that’s why.

582
00:48:34,793 --> 00:48:36,740
I saved him.

583
00:48:37,040 --> 00:48:39,860
I saved him
when he had no money or nothing.

584
00:48:40,086 --> 00:48:42,780
He doesn’t even appreciate it and
dares to play hard to get with me.

585
00:48:43,820 --> 00:48:45,613
I must have kept him in check
before marriage.

586
00:48:46,640 --> 00:48:48,295
Just because I keep being kind to him,

587
00:48:48,320 --> 00:48:49,460
he thinks it's right.

588
00:48:53,730 --> 00:48:55,370
I hate that the most.

589
00:48:56,880 --> 00:48:58,375
What, kindness?

590
00:49:00,415 --> 00:49:01,661
Anyway...

591
00:49:04,840 --> 00:49:07,313
I want to see what his
attitude is when I‘m not around.

592
00:49:07,466 --> 00:49:09,506
Oh, this is surprisingly fun.

593
00:49:09,540 --> 00:49:10,706
This is the place,

594
00:49:10,910 --> 00:49:11,910
right?

595
00:49:13,400 --> 00:49:15,166
What are you doing?
Come here.

596
00:49:22,774 --> 00:49:24,407
Are you really going in?

597
00:49:29,220 --> 00:49:30,247
Push it.

598
00:49:50,213 --> 00:49:51,279
Open it.

599
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:19,940
Oh, it's so cold.

600
00:50:22,800 --> 00:50:27,286
Wow, this place hasn't changed at all.

601
00:50:33,603 --> 00:50:36,523
It reminds you of old times
when we were in here, right?

602
00:50:39,563 --> 00:50:41,163
I'm a little scared here.

603
00:50:42,090 --> 00:50:44,656
What's so scary, you dummy?

604
00:50:46,370 --> 00:50:48,270
I'm here,
so what’s there to be scared of?

605
00:50:51,109 --> 00:50:52,183
From now on,

606
00:50:53,000 --> 00:50:55,850
If I signal like this with my chin,

607
00:50:56,270 --> 00:50:58,403
you have to come in here and wait,
no matter what.

608
00:50:59,123 --> 00:51:00,163
Got it?

609
00:51:01,126 --> 00:51:02,460
Like a subordinate to you?

610
00:51:03,526 --> 00:51:04,906
Like a subordinate...

611
00:51:05,666 --> 00:51:06,786
and a slave.

612
00:51:10,646 --> 00:51:11,993
You like me, don't you?

613
00:51:13,399 --> 00:51:14,320
Yes.

614
00:51:15,006 --> 00:51:16,512
Then you're my slave.

615
00:51:16,866 --> 00:51:18,032
Understood?

616
00:51:19,550 --> 00:51:20,550
Yes.

617
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:24,533
Then kiss me.

618
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:26,693
What do you mean by kissing you?

619
00:51:26,873 --> 00:51:28,693
You said you like me, right?

620
00:51:31,453 --> 00:51:33,966
Okay, close your eyes.

621
00:51:35,346 --> 00:51:36,446
Okay.

622
00:51:38,774 --> 00:51:40,132
I’m closing my eyes.

623
00:52:00,366 --> 00:52:01,520
I don’t think...

624
00:52:02,732 --> 00:52:04,520
I’m ready for marriage right now.

625
00:52:05,870 --> 00:52:07,120
So, it's better not to do it.

626
00:52:08,676 --> 00:52:10,549
It‘s not your fault.

627
00:52:11,122 --> 00:52:12,256
It's mine.

628
00:52:12,589 --> 00:52:13,669
That’s why...

629
00:52:14,589 --> 00:52:15,989
I have to leave.

630
00:52:17,788 --> 00:52:19,902
But having you by my side all this time…

631
00:52:20,942 --> 00:52:22,515
It made me truly happy.

632
00:52:24,830 --> 00:52:25,923
Goodbye.

633
00:52:33,416 --> 00:52:35,150
It's so sad, right?

634
00:52:36,870 --> 00:52:37,870
Yes.

635
00:52:38,783 --> 00:52:40,016
Seriously,

636
00:52:40,603 --> 00:52:44,145
He won't know what to do
after watching this video.

637
00:52:44,170 --> 00:52:45,956
Because it's so sad.

638
00:52:46,520 --> 00:52:49,730
{\an8}<i>Sung-jin, watch this video.</i>

639
00:52:47,670 --> 00:52:48,906
It's so sad.

640
00:52:54,436 --> 00:52:55,736
Is this one a bit too much?

641
00:52:56,083 --> 00:52:57,716
Well, it's very cold.

642
00:52:59,336 --> 00:53:00,475
But,

643
00:53:00,500 --> 00:53:02,913
Is it Schubert?

644
00:53:03,300 --> 00:53:04,328
Yeah.

645
00:53:04,353 --> 00:53:07,026
Oh, you have no idea
how stubborn he is.

646
00:53:07,756 --> 00:53:09,629
He says Schubert's music is the saddest,

647
00:53:09,850 --> 00:53:11,236
and that's why it's the best.

648
00:53:12,850 --> 00:53:13,920
Right.

649
00:53:14,120 --> 00:53:15,249
Gotta make it messy,

650
00:53:15,250 --> 00:53:16,933
to make it feel like I left suddenly.

651
00:53:24,663 --> 00:53:27,606
He says that it is so sad that
he doesn’t even feel sad anymore.

652
00:53:28,113 --> 00:53:29,306
Did you pack everything?

653
00:53:29,880 --> 00:53:30,880
Yeah.

654
00:53:34,120 --> 00:53:35,073
Okay.

655
00:53:35,520 --> 00:53:36,973
So heavy.

656
00:53:40,420 --> 00:53:41,766
You should give me the key too.

657
00:53:53,050 --> 00:53:54,850
How long are you going to stay there?

658
00:53:56,120 --> 00:53:57,850
I don't know. Three days, tops.

659
00:53:58,120 --> 00:53:59,483
Because there's practice,

660
00:53:59,850 --> 00:54:01,423
might as well watch my diet.

661
00:54:02,609 --> 00:54:03,796
I'm going in.

662
00:54:11,070 --> 00:54:13,096
Put the bookshelf back properly.

663
00:54:53,266 --> 00:54:54,559
I'm leaving.

664
00:54:54,584 --> 00:54:55,537
Okay.

665
00:55:05,450 --> 00:55:07,290
<i>No service.</i>

666
00:55:41,870 --> 00:55:43,800
Sung-jin, it's me.

667
00:55:44,400 --> 00:55:45,520
Did I surprise you?

668
00:55:46,140 --> 00:55:49,226
I'm leaving now.

669
00:55:49,700 --> 00:55:50,720
For Berlin.

670
00:55:51,693 --> 00:55:53,293
I don't know...

671
00:55:54,250 --> 00:55:56,500
- My relationship with you...
- Oh, so sad.

672
00:55:57,420 --> 00:55:58,850
I'm not sure about it anymore.

673
00:55:59,720 --> 00:56:01,359
I don’t understand you.

674
00:56:01,973 --> 00:56:03,526
So I'm really angry, and…

675
00:56:03,799 --> 00:56:06,125
I keep doubting everything,
and it worries me.

676
00:56:06,150 --> 00:56:07,883
Please let me go.

677
00:56:09,143 --> 00:56:10,910
It was my fault.

678
00:56:13,800 --> 00:56:16,783
Please let me go home.
I'm begging you.

679
00:57:12,432 --> 00:57:15,325
Ah... you look like you're
about to die from sadness.

680
00:57:17,520 --> 00:57:18,805
Let’s see...

681
00:57:50,099 --> 00:57:52,965
Sung-jin, I'm here.

682
00:57:54,599 --> 00:57:56,720
Sung-jin, I'm right here.

683
00:57:59,370 --> 00:58:01,120
Sung-jin.

684
00:58:01,200 --> 00:58:03,638
I'm here! I said I'm here!

685
00:58:07,958 --> 00:58:10,045
I'm locked in here!

686
00:58:11,212 --> 00:58:12,345
Hey!

687
00:58:16,666 --> 00:58:18,146
Sung-jin!

688
00:58:18,300 --> 00:58:20,300
I'm locked in here.

689
00:58:20,606 --> 00:58:22,186
Sung-jin.

690
00:58:22,966 --> 00:58:24,666
I'm telling you,
I'm locked in here!

691
00:58:25,932 --> 00:58:28,000
Sung-jin, Sung-jin!

692
00:58:32,671 --> 00:58:35,145
Sung-jin! Sung-jin!

693
01:00:43,089 --> 01:00:45,176
What the hell took you so long?!

694
01:00:46,123 --> 01:00:48,043
I totally freaked out,
thinking I was trapped.

695
01:00:53,280 --> 01:00:54,970
Are you doing well?

696
01:00:56,239 --> 01:00:57,145
You...

697
01:00:59,659 --> 01:01:00,925
How did you get in?

698
01:01:05,019 --> 01:01:08,225
How did you get into our house?

699
01:01:08,540 --> 01:01:09,880
I'm drunk.

700
01:01:11,973 --> 01:01:14,386
It’s because Sung-jin kept making me drink.

701
01:01:15,426 --> 01:01:18,913
I told him I can’t drink wine,
but he keeps making me!

702
01:01:21,080 --> 01:01:22,673
I guess he just wants to fuck me.

703
01:01:23,520 --> 01:01:24,580
Are you out of your mind?

704
01:01:26,373 --> 01:01:29,400
I kind of changed the key.

705
01:01:30,770 --> 01:01:32,313
Just to mess with you.

706
01:01:34,193 --> 01:01:35,686
You must be really pissed…

707
01:01:36,673 --> 01:01:38,346
And totally freaked out, right?

708
01:01:40,966 --> 01:01:42,439
Want me to let you out now?

709
01:01:58,910 --> 01:02:02,041
So… if I let you out,
will you forgive me?

710
01:02:15,140 --> 01:02:16,813
So you're gonna forgive me?

711
01:02:22,220 --> 01:02:24,633
Then I guess I’ll have to do
something you can’t forgive.

712
01:02:25,370 --> 01:02:26,426
What?

713
01:02:28,740 --> 01:02:29,740
What?

714
01:02:33,393 --> 01:02:34,500
What is it?

715
01:02:45,200 --> 01:02:46,227
Mi-joo.

716
01:02:46,740 --> 01:02:48,413
I‘m completely drunk.

717
01:02:49,820 --> 01:02:52,400
I knew it, wine is poison for me.

718
01:02:52,953 --> 01:02:55,560
Sung-jin… what…
what are you two doing right now?

719
01:02:55,585 --> 01:02:56,886
Mi-joo, don’t do this.

720
01:02:56,911 --> 01:02:59,220
You.. you’re being childish, huh?

721
01:02:59,600 --> 01:03:00,686
Mi-joo.

722
01:03:02,400 --> 01:03:03,517
Don‘t do this.

723
01:03:08,151 --> 01:03:09,400
Don't do this!

724
01:03:09,817 --> 01:03:10,870
Stop it!

725
01:03:11,340 --> 01:03:14,310
Mi-joo, you don’t like being
touched by men, remember?

726
01:03:14,837 --> 01:03:16,570
Mi-joo, please don't.

727
01:03:16,804 --> 01:03:18,517
Stop it! Stop it!

728
01:03:18,542 --> 01:03:19,680
Stop touching her there!

729
01:03:19,880 --> 01:03:21,250
Please stop it, Mi-joo.

730
01:03:22,250 --> 01:03:23,250
Stop.

731
01:03:25,400 --> 01:03:28,540
Yes… Yes… That’s good.

732
01:03:28,910 --> 01:03:30,140
You did well.

733
01:03:40,055 --> 01:03:42,142
Don't do this,
are you crazy?

734
01:03:42,310 --> 01:03:43,381
Are you insane?!

735
01:03:44,650 --> 01:03:45,850
Mi-joo.

736
01:03:48,243 --> 01:03:50,653
Sung-jin, have you lost your mind?!

737
01:04:18,494 --> 01:04:20,388
- Why did you take everything off?!
- Stop!

738
01:04:26,600 --> 01:04:28,000
Stop it!

739
01:04:30,280 --> 01:04:32,600
Stop it, stop it!

740
01:04:33,160 --> 01:04:34,486
Stop it!

741
01:04:35,456 --> 01:04:37,850
No! Stop! Stop it!

742
01:04:41,676 --> 01:04:43,925
Stop... Stop...

743
01:05:06,571 --> 01:05:12,430
<i>7 months ago</i>

744
01:05:17,440 --> 01:05:22,360
<i>I miss you</i>

745
01:05:25,340 --> 01:05:28,740
I thought you guys hated this place.

746
01:05:29,970 --> 01:05:30,970
Why, teacher?

747
01:05:31,480 --> 01:05:36,040
Didn’t I nag you a lot when
you took lessons in this house?

748
01:05:37,570 --> 01:05:40,950
Well, thanks to that,
we all make a living playing the cello.

749
01:05:41,880 --> 01:05:45,220
If Su-yeon buys this house,
that’d be great for me.

750
01:05:47,766 --> 01:05:49,850
It’s pretty much the same here.

751
01:05:50,910 --> 01:05:51,740
Yeah.

752
01:05:51,916 --> 01:05:53,666
It’s because the bookshelf
is just so pretty.

753
01:05:54,770 --> 01:05:57,480
So, is the inside still the same too?

754
01:05:58,710 --> 01:05:59,710
What?

755
01:06:01,420 --> 01:06:03,146
Did you think I wouldn’t know?

756
01:06:03,620 --> 01:06:07,806
I knew from the beginning that
you guys were going in there.

757
01:06:09,510 --> 01:06:10,375
I’m sorry.

758
01:06:10,400 --> 01:06:12,073
What is there to be sorry about?

759
01:06:13,220 --> 01:06:16,406
Back then, I thought
it was just a kid’s game,

760
01:06:16,570 --> 01:06:19,000
I didn’t realize
you’d been dating so long

761
01:06:19,280 --> 01:06:22,288
and were looking for a new house together.

762
01:06:23,940 --> 01:06:26,650
By the way,
what is this space in here?

763
01:06:27,620 --> 01:06:29,714
I've always wondered.

764
01:06:31,970 --> 01:06:35,973
My father made it
when he was building the house.

765
01:06:36,080 --> 01:06:37,425
My father...

766
01:06:37,450 --> 01:06:40,940
You know that notorious Unit 731
from the Japanese occupation?

767
01:06:41,400 --> 01:06:43,600
He was a medical officer there.

768
01:06:45,280 --> 01:06:48,216
So, it seems like
he did some bad things.

769
01:06:49,880 --> 01:06:54,553
Maybe that's why he was always anxious
and wanted to stay hidden.

770
01:06:55,140 --> 01:06:56,380
When he got home from work,

771
01:06:57,280 --> 01:07:00,370
he would always spy on Mom
and us sisters through the mirror,

772
01:07:01,050 --> 01:07:03,770
then call us over

773
01:07:04,200 --> 01:07:06,200
and put shackles on us.

774
01:07:07,050 --> 01:07:08,050
Right.

775
01:07:08,450 --> 01:07:11,370
The shackles are still in there, right?

776
01:07:12,270 --> 01:07:13,296
Are they?

777
01:07:25,632 --> 01:07:26,792
How is it?

778
01:07:28,080 --> 01:07:29,219
I like it!

779
01:07:29,553 --> 01:07:32,499
It's super cool and exciting!

780
01:07:33,450 --> 01:07:35,020
I always wanted to try it.

781
01:07:37,400 --> 01:07:38,850
Give me the key.

782
01:07:49,236 --> 01:07:51,889
Hey, what are you doing?

783
01:07:52,310 --> 01:07:55,276
Bring it here and untie me.

784
01:07:58,800 --> 01:08:00,600
What if I don't?

785
01:08:01,650 --> 01:08:03,850
You will.

786
01:08:05,200 --> 01:08:06,710
I trust you.

787
01:08:13,370 --> 01:08:14,696
Trust me?

788
01:08:16,370 --> 01:08:17,370
Yes.

789
01:08:18,376 --> 01:08:20,340
Only you.

790
01:08:30,857 --> 01:08:32,277
I won’t untie you.

791
01:08:34,450 --> 01:08:37,910
Yes, you will.

792
01:08:40,110 --> 01:08:41,903
Because, I'm yours.

793
01:08:47,149 --> 01:08:49,029
<i>She</i>

794
01:08:51,306 --> 01:08:52,544
Hello.

795
01:08:52,569 --> 01:08:53,569
<i>It's me.</i>

796
01:08:53,620 --> 01:08:54,595
<i>What's up?</i>

797
01:08:54,620 --> 01:08:55,739
It's finished.

798
01:08:55,740 --> 01:08:58,299
I was just recording a video
to send to you.

799
01:08:58,959 --> 01:09:00,880
<i>Ah, you worked so hard.</i>

800
01:09:01,620 --> 01:09:04,685
<i>By the way, I have something to tell you.</i>

801
01:09:05,680 --> 01:09:06,786
What's it?

802
01:09:08,220 --> 01:09:12,106
<i>When I come to Seoul,
do you know who I will be with?</i>

803
01:09:12,620 --> 01:09:14,019
With who?

804
01:09:14,180 --> 01:09:15,666
<i>A man.</i>

805
01:09:17,640 --> 01:09:18,946
<i>The man I’m going to marry.</i>

806
01:09:19,520 --> 01:09:20,780
<i>I met him here.</i>

807
01:09:21,080 --> 01:09:22,510
<i>We’ll come back together.</i>

808
01:09:23,747 --> 01:09:24,831
Wow...

809
01:09:26,813 --> 01:09:31,487
<i>Yeah, it’s 'Wow', right?</i>

810
01:09:35,842 --> 01:09:36,885
Wow...

811
01:09:42,995 --> 01:09:44,288
Then, what about me?

812
01:09:45,740 --> 01:09:47,000
<i>You know.</i>

813
01:09:49,000 --> 01:09:50,000
I know?

814
01:09:50,540 --> 01:09:51,880
<i>Congratulate me.</i>

815
01:09:52,740 --> 01:09:54,080
<i>I'm getting married.</i>

816
01:09:54,301 --> 01:09:56,101
<i>Living with a man.</i>

817
01:09:56,680 --> 01:10:00,600
<i>A real life that others recognize.</i>

818
01:10:02,480 --> 01:10:03,800
A real life?

819
01:10:04,220 --> 01:10:05,310
<i>It’s a real life,</i>

820
01:10:05,460 --> 01:10:06,540
<i>from now on.</i>

821
01:10:06,740 --> 01:10:09,253
If that's real life...

822
01:10:12,546 --> 01:10:13,586
then what about me?

823
01:10:14,620 --> 01:10:17,000
Was it fake with me?

824
01:10:22,800 --> 01:10:25,433
<i>I’ll just be honest. It's okay, right?</i>

825
01:10:26,246 --> 01:10:27,439
<i>You were...</i>

826
01:10:28,712 --> 01:10:33,025
<i>just a tool for me to know where I’m
sensitive and where I like to be touched.</i>

827
01:10:33,050 --> 01:10:34,840
<i>I was your tool too.</i>

828
01:10:35,000 --> 01:10:38,086
<i>We both knew it, didn’t we?</i>

829
01:10:38,812 --> 01:10:40,843
<i>Let’s stop following each other.</i>

830
01:10:43,770 --> 01:10:44,798
<b>And then...</b>

831
01:11:01,370 --> 01:11:03,134
You think I’m crazy, don’t you?

832
01:11:04,536 --> 01:11:06,509
I wasn‘t supposed to come here.

833
01:11:08,482 --> 01:11:09,869
But I‘ve come here twice already.

834
01:11:58,050 --> 01:11:59,361
When you are out...

835
01:12:01,209 --> 01:12:03,361
you're going to hand me over
to the police, right?

836
01:12:03,800 --> 01:12:05,633
No, no.

837
01:12:06,560 --> 01:12:08,641
No, no, Mi-joo.

838
01:12:08,666 --> 01:12:10,547
I made the mistake first, right?

839
01:12:10,572 --> 01:12:12,519
I won’t make it an issue at all.

840
01:12:12,520 --> 01:12:14,221
Seriously, I won’t!
Please stop it here.

841
01:12:14,246 --> 01:12:16,580
Please open it, will you?

842
01:12:17,650 --> 01:12:20,690
Yeah, well, there's
nothing I can say about that.

843
01:12:24,320 --> 01:12:25,750
But you know...

844
01:12:27,003 --> 01:12:32,013
I finally understand what you were saying.

845
01:12:34,540 --> 01:12:36,210
About real life.

846
01:12:36,750 --> 01:12:39,825
The real isn't the real real,

847
01:12:39,850 --> 01:12:42,364
it's what everyone thinks it is.

848
01:12:42,550 --> 01:12:43,583
Right?

849
01:12:47,060 --> 01:12:48,176
I got that.

850
01:12:49,560 --> 01:12:50,646
Also,

851
01:12:52,020 --> 01:12:53,493
that life...

852
01:12:56,230 --> 01:12:57,860
I think I need it too.

853
01:12:59,820 --> 01:13:01,400
What do you mean?

854
01:13:01,950 --> 01:13:03,251
That man...

855
01:13:04,710 --> 01:13:06,336
I will have him.

856
01:13:08,090 --> 01:13:11,309
I will live that real life.

857
01:13:14,230 --> 01:13:15,243
What?

858
01:13:16,420 --> 01:13:17,550
Sorry.

859
01:13:22,653 --> 01:13:24,760
I think you should stay there forever.

860
01:13:26,090 --> 01:13:27,090
Mi-joo.

861
01:13:27,300 --> 01:13:28,260
Mi-joo, Mi-joo!

862
01:13:28,261 --> 01:13:30,269
No, I was wrong.

863
01:13:30,270 --> 01:13:31,639
I was wrong,

864
01:13:31,640 --> 01:13:33,440
it’s all my fault!

865
01:13:47,990 --> 01:13:48,990
What‘s wrong?

866
01:13:50,080 --> 01:13:52,790
Suddenly, only hot water
is coming out of the shower.

867
01:13:53,000 --> 01:13:54,266
- Hot water?
- It‘s okay.

868
01:13:54,620 --> 01:13:57,140
- Why?
- It‘s really fine. It wasn’t hot at all.

869
01:13:57,165 --> 01:13:58,670
- Are you alright?
- You should go out.

870
01:14:04,340 --> 01:14:08,133
We need to tear down
the whole wall to get to the pipe.

871
01:14:09,600 --> 01:14:13,140
Or we can simply cut off
the main water line

872
01:14:13,600 --> 01:14:15,690
and connect a new one.

873
01:14:16,192 --> 01:14:19,270
That’s a lot of work too,
but still the better option.

874
01:14:21,150 --> 01:14:24,780
Seriously, is this place
a bomb shelter or something?

875
01:14:25,530 --> 01:14:28,159
These walls are way too thick...

876
01:14:28,160 --> 01:14:30,710
- you can’t tear this down!
- Here, here, here!

877
01:14:31,030 --> 01:14:32,289
There’s someone in here!

878
01:14:32,290 --> 01:14:33,120
Hey, man…

879
01:14:33,290 --> 01:14:34,290
Hey!

880
01:14:35,250 --> 01:14:36,960
Cut off the main water line ?

881
01:14:37,750 --> 01:14:39,460
No, no!

882
01:14:39,750 --> 01:14:41,591
If there's no other choice,
then do it that way.

883
01:14:41,616 --> 01:14:42,629
When can we start?

884
01:14:42,630 --> 01:14:44,670
Today, I can start right away.

885
01:14:45,010 --> 01:14:47,009
No, no.

886
01:14:47,010 --> 01:14:48,129
No!

887
01:14:48,130 --> 01:14:49,130
No!

888
01:14:50,090 --> 01:14:56,680
But hey, don’t you hear this ‘woong’ sound?

889
01:14:57,230 --> 01:14:59,099
Woong...

890
01:14:59,100 --> 01:15:01,770
No way! No!

891
01:15:08,700 --> 01:15:10,570
What the… fu…

892
01:15:11,320 --> 01:15:12,920
Ah! That scared me, damn!

893
01:15:16,790 --> 01:15:18,620
Ah… so creepy.

894
01:15:19,170 --> 01:15:20,210
I'm heading out.

895
01:15:20,710 --> 01:15:24,190
Sung-jin, Sung-jin!
That was me, I did it!

896
01:15:29,800 --> 01:15:31,090
So weird!

897
01:15:32,180 --> 01:15:33,420
There are no immigration records.

898
01:15:33,560 --> 01:15:35,930
So she hasn’t left the country.

899
01:15:36,900 --> 01:15:38,559
No card usage at all

900
01:15:38,560 --> 01:15:40,189
her phone is still switched off,

901
01:15:40,190 --> 01:15:42,020
and she hasn't contacted me even once.

902
01:15:44,360 --> 01:15:45,610
I'm her mom.

903
01:15:45,860 --> 01:15:47,149
I know Su-yeon well.

904
01:15:47,150 --> 01:15:49,150
Su-yeon would never do
something like this.

905
01:15:49,450 --> 01:15:50,660
There’s something going on.

906
01:15:51,953 --> 01:15:53,073
She’s not the type of person

907
01:15:53,360 --> 01:15:57,200
who could just disappear like this
without any reason.

908
01:15:58,910 --> 01:16:00,249
Right? Darling.

909
01:16:00,250 --> 01:16:01,460
Don’t you think so too?

910
01:16:02,330 --> 01:16:03,330
Yeah.

911
01:16:06,300 --> 01:16:07,300
So

912
01:16:09,170 --> 01:16:10,800
I called the police.

913
01:16:11,800 --> 01:16:13,720
I should have called them earlier.

914
01:16:17,101 --> 01:16:19,020
The police will be at
your house tomorrow.

915
01:16:19,640 --> 01:16:20,980
To our house?

916
01:16:22,230 --> 01:16:23,650
Don’t take it the wrong way.

917
01:16:24,520 --> 01:16:26,440
They're not doing this
because they suspect you,

918
01:16:27,730 --> 01:16:30,530
they're just making sure.

919
01:16:32,820 --> 01:16:33,820
Director,

920
01:16:38,700 --> 01:16:40,910
are you suspecting me now?

921
01:16:45,630 --> 01:16:46,630
Suspicion?

922
01:16:47,630 --> 01:16:49,260
What suspicion is there?

923
01:16:52,970 --> 01:16:55,260
Ah, look at him, searching so carelessly.

924
01:16:56,430 --> 01:16:57,930
No wonder he's a civil servant.

925
01:16:59,640 --> 01:17:01,480
What is it that he's searching for
so carelessly?

926
01:17:02,350 --> 01:17:04,190
Is he looking for the body I buried?

927
01:17:05,150 --> 01:17:06,150
Oh, come on,

928
01:17:06,480 --> 01:17:08,230
don't take it personally.

929
01:17:08,780 --> 01:17:11,070
We're only following orders.

930
01:17:11,990 --> 01:17:13,489
In fact, while doing this,

931
01:17:13,490 --> 01:17:15,740
observing your expression
is part of our technique

932
01:17:17,830 --> 01:17:18,990
just to see how you react.

933
01:17:21,290 --> 01:17:22,410
How's my reaction?

934
01:17:24,580 --> 01:17:25,580
Clear.

935
01:17:26,170 --> 01:17:27,170
Clean.

936
01:17:28,130 --> 01:17:29,130
Pure.

937
01:18:47,486 --> 01:18:49,180
Don't make fun of
me because it's small.

938
01:19:08,270 --> 01:19:10,551
Doesn't it feel too stuffy here?

939
01:19:12,440 --> 01:19:13,980
It's more comfy.

940
01:19:15,230 --> 01:19:16,610
Our house is too big.

941
01:19:20,870 --> 01:19:22,070
I don't like that saying

942
01:19:23,280 --> 01:19:24,280
'Our house'.

943
01:19:37,220 --> 01:19:38,880
1117

944
01:19:40,930 --> 01:19:41,930
What?

945
01:19:42,600 --> 01:19:44,890
The front door code is 1117.

946
01:19:48,390 --> 01:19:49,560
What about that number?

947
01:19:50,690 --> 01:19:52,770
It's the same as Su-yeon's birthday.

948
01:19:55,013 --> 01:19:55,926
really?

949
01:19:57,650 --> 01:20:01,790
I’m just using the one
the previous resident set up.

950
01:20:03,660 --> 01:20:05,790
Interesting,
that’s her birthday.

951
01:20:07,620 --> 01:20:10,210
I'm not really good at
changing those kinds of things.

952
01:20:22,583 --> 01:20:23,436
Yes.

953
01:20:23,930 --> 01:20:25,003
Take a look at this.

954
01:20:26,986 --> 01:20:28,865
Director,
I've seen this a hundred times.

955
01:20:28,890 --> 01:20:30,356
Wait a second,
I want you to look at something.

956
01:20:32,020 --> 01:20:34,396
Oh, it's here.

957
01:20:36,020 --> 01:20:38,690
Look at the mirror behind Su-yeon.

958
01:20:43,360 --> 01:20:46,030
There's a hand.

959
01:20:47,160 --> 01:20:48,330
Someone else's hand.

960
01:20:50,120 --> 01:20:53,520
I never noticed this before because
I was always looking at Su-yeon's face.

961
01:20:53,750 --> 01:20:56,290
But today,
I suddenly had a strange feeling.

962
01:20:57,096 --> 01:20:58,130
So I looked again

963
01:20:58,750 --> 01:20:59,750
and found a hand.

964
01:21:00,010 --> 01:21:01,010
Do you see it?

965
01:21:03,340 --> 01:21:04,340
Yes.

966
01:21:05,470 --> 01:21:10,140
There was someone with her when she left.

967
01:21:15,560 --> 01:21:16,560
What's up.

968
01:21:18,020 --> 01:21:19,900
Did you suddenly miss me?

969
01:21:20,740 --> 01:21:21,740
Yeah.

970
01:21:23,400 --> 01:21:24,490
That's romantic.

971
01:21:24,990 --> 01:21:28,330
Don't ring the bell,
just enter the code and come in.

972
01:21:28,700 --> 01:21:29,990
1117

973
01:21:43,760 --> 01:21:46,510
No one's been particularly mean to me.

974
01:21:47,090 --> 01:21:50,260
Everyone seems really nice
and treats me well.

975
01:21:51,060 --> 01:21:54,890
I've gotten really close
with the cello team

976
01:21:56,060 --> 01:21:58,893
and last time, I even had a
meal with the principal cellist.

977
01:21:59,610 --> 01:22:01,650
Ah, she's really kind,

978
01:22:02,360 --> 01:22:05,576
and how come someone uses the bow
so smoothly and with such charisma?

979
01:22:05,936 --> 01:22:08,076
I might learn by watching that.

980
01:22:09,080 --> 01:22:11,870
Ah, there's one person.

981
01:22:12,500 --> 01:22:14,079
I'm talking about
the concertmaster.

982
01:22:14,326 --> 01:22:16,553
You know her personality.

983
01:22:16,960 --> 01:22:20,089
She always blames the strings,

984
01:22:20,090 --> 01:22:22,090
even when it’s the wind section’s fault.

985
01:22:22,630 --> 01:22:26,549
If it weren’t for her, our orchestra
would have a great atmosphere, right?

986
01:22:32,600 --> 01:22:33,613
Why aren't you eating?

987
01:22:42,270 --> 01:22:43,440
I need to ask you something.

988
01:22:44,570 --> 01:22:45,570
What is it?

989
01:22:46,280 --> 01:22:48,400
You were with Su-yeon
when she left home, right?

990
01:22:51,990 --> 01:22:53,370
What are you talking about?

991
01:22:53,830 --> 01:22:55,450
I saw your wrist in the mirror.

992
01:22:58,170 --> 01:22:59,210
That bracelet.

993
01:23:00,080 --> 01:23:01,790
The one with the blue stones.

994
01:23:03,090 --> 01:23:04,340
Didn't you wear it today?

995
01:23:07,130 --> 01:23:08,130
Blue stones?

996
01:23:22,770 --> 01:23:23,770
This one?

997
01:23:34,830 --> 01:23:35,830
You're right.

998
01:23:38,160 --> 01:23:41,000
I was in her room the day she left.

999
01:23:43,880 --> 01:23:47,920
So you've been lying all this time?

1000
01:23:49,720 --> 01:23:51,179
So what you said about Su-yeon
contacting you after a long time

1001
01:23:51,180 --> 01:23:52,340
and that you weren’t close,

1002
01:23:52,930 --> 01:23:54,680
and that this was your
first time coming to our house,

1003
01:23:55,930 --> 01:23:56,930
all of it was a lie.

1004
01:23:59,190 --> 01:24:00,190
I'm sorry.

1005
01:24:01,480 --> 01:24:04,940
But can you just not say
it's 'our house'?

1006
01:24:05,190 --> 01:24:06,190
What?

1007
01:24:14,530 --> 01:24:15,530
What's the purpose?

1008
01:24:15,531 --> 01:24:16,691
Why are you doing this to me?

1009
01:24:18,620 --> 01:24:19,790
She told me to do it.

1010
01:24:20,330 --> 01:24:22,540
She asked me to fix the house, so I did.

1011
01:24:22,580 --> 01:24:25,880
She told me to help her leave, so I did.

1012
01:24:26,250 --> 01:24:28,880
She asked me to fill in for her, so I did.

1013
01:24:30,470 --> 01:24:32,760
I only did what I was told to do.

1014
01:24:33,090 --> 01:24:34,170
What?

1015
01:24:34,720 --> 01:24:36,800
Are you a servant to follow
whatever she tells you to do?

1016
01:24:37,516 --> 01:24:38,542
Are you her slave?

1017
01:24:40,060 --> 01:24:41,480
Am I really a slave?

1018
01:24:42,730 --> 01:24:45,400
It seems like the only thing
I decided on my own

1019
01:24:45,860 --> 01:24:47,650
was sleeping with you.

1020
01:24:55,200 --> 01:24:56,530
Where is Su-yeon right now?

1021
01:24:57,410 --> 01:24:58,410
You must know.

1022
01:24:58,830 --> 01:25:00,290
I really don't know that either.

1023
01:25:00,930 --> 01:25:02,080
Don't lie.

1024
01:25:06,090 --> 01:25:07,500
You two like each other, don't you?

1025
01:25:07,880 --> 01:25:08,960
You mean I like her?

1026
01:25:13,510 --> 01:25:15,260
I have seen all the photos

1027
01:25:15,760 --> 01:25:17,010
you two took.

1028
01:25:19,060 --> 01:25:21,270
What are you saying?

1029
01:25:21,770 --> 01:25:26,020
It's nothing serious,
just kids' stuff.

1030
01:25:26,310 --> 01:25:28,400
Like a friendship pact or something.

1031
01:25:29,150 --> 01:25:30,570
Stop lying.

1032
01:25:32,990 --> 01:25:34,240
Tell me.

1033
01:25:34,820 --> 01:25:36,156
Where is Su-yeon right now?

1034
01:25:36,570 --> 01:25:38,330
I really don't know.

1035
01:25:40,700 --> 01:25:44,040
I really, really don't know.

1036
01:26:00,563 --> 01:26:03,050
I'm going to cut off the water.

1037
01:26:08,560 --> 01:26:10,020
It's me.

1038
01:26:26,116 --> 01:26:27,189
It's me.

1039
01:26:31,550 --> 01:26:32,550
Turn on the water.

1040
01:26:34,550 --> 01:26:36,523
Okay.

1041
01:26:38,416 --> 01:26:39,956
It's me!

1042
01:27:09,040 --> 01:27:10,040
Over here!

1043
01:27:12,210 --> 01:27:13,300
Su-yeon, is that you?

1044
01:27:20,510 --> 01:27:21,510
Turn it off.

1045
01:27:31,360 --> 01:27:32,203
Su-yeon!

1046
01:27:34,817 --> 01:27:36,617
Are you by any chance
inside this house?

1047
01:27:36,798 --> 01:27:38,341
Over here, over here!

1048
01:27:38,900 --> 01:27:39,950
Are you locked in?

1049
01:27:41,160 --> 01:27:42,619
I'm locked in.
Help me!

1050
01:27:42,620 --> 01:27:44,580
Help me, Sung-jin.

1051
01:27:45,700 --> 01:27:46,700
Su-yeon.

1052
01:27:48,460 --> 01:27:49,500
Are you in here?

1053
01:27:50,330 --> 01:27:51,330
Su-yeon...

1054
01:27:52,580 --> 01:27:53,919
Sung-jin, here.
Right here.

1055
01:27:53,920 --> 01:27:55,919
Right in front of you.

1056
01:27:55,920 --> 01:27:56,855
Right in front of you.

1057
01:27:56,879 --> 01:27:58,470
Over here! Over here!

1058
01:28:08,350 --> 01:28:10,390
I’m here. Right here.

1059
01:28:11,600 --> 01:28:12,600
Su-yeon.

1060
01:28:13,650 --> 01:28:14,650
Are you here?

1061
01:28:14,690 --> 01:28:17,740
I'm standing right here!

1062
01:28:26,870 --> 01:28:28,040
So, you’re in here.

1063
01:28:28,870 --> 01:28:30,830
Yes.

1064
01:28:53,650 --> 01:28:54,690
Sung-jin, what’s wrong?

1065
01:28:56,190 --> 01:28:57,190
Huh?

1066
01:28:58,769 --> 01:28:59,823
Why?

1067
01:29:07,620 --> 01:29:08,620
What's wrong?

1068
01:29:11,660 --> 01:29:12,660
Why?

1069
01:29:19,093 --> 01:29:20,880
So, you must have seen
everything from there?

1070
01:29:22,010 --> 01:29:23,010
Right?

1071
01:29:24,390 --> 01:29:25,890
What I did with Mi-joo.

1072
01:29:28,430 --> 01:29:29,640
You saw it all.

1073
01:29:31,270 --> 01:29:32,636
It doesn’t matter.
Just let me out.

1074
01:29:33,016 --> 01:29:34,063
I don't care.

1075
01:29:34,576 --> 01:29:36,230
I don't care anymore.
Let me out of here.

1076
01:29:36,270 --> 01:29:37,649
Let me out!

1077
01:29:37,650 --> 01:29:38,889
So, Mi-joo..

1078
01:29:43,269 --> 01:29:45,570
came here knowing everything, right?

1079
01:29:47,830 --> 01:29:49,563
She did it on purpose to show you.

1080
01:29:51,813 --> 01:29:52,840
Right?

1081
01:29:54,710 --> 01:29:56,746
Even though she knew
you were watching.

1082
01:29:59,046 --> 01:30:00,233
I don't care.

1083
01:30:00,460 --> 01:30:02,494
Really, I don't.

1084
01:30:02,519 --> 01:30:04,747
- Ah, fuck!
- It really doesn't matter.

1085
01:30:04,772 --> 01:30:06,372
I seriously don’t care.

1086
01:30:06,919 --> 01:30:07,930
You two…

1087
01:30:08,970 --> 01:30:10,354
just what are you up to?

1088
01:30:10,379 --> 01:30:11,889
Please, help me.

1089
01:30:11,890 --> 01:30:13,309
Sung-jin, help me.

1090
01:30:13,310 --> 01:30:14,480
Please, help me.

1091
01:30:14,730 --> 01:30:16,190
Help me... please!

1092
01:30:17,310 --> 01:30:20,803
Ah, please... help me!

1093
01:30:23,436 --> 01:30:25,860
Please let me out…

1094
01:30:28,200 --> 01:30:29,870
It's her fault.

1095
01:30:30,620 --> 01:30:34,460
She used me and then dumped me.

1096
01:30:34,790 --> 01:30:36,533
So you locked her up
because of that?

1097
01:30:37,040 --> 01:30:38,250
I didn’t lock her up.

1098
01:30:39,330 --> 01:30:41,130
She walked in there on her own.

1099
01:30:42,130 --> 01:30:44,880
But something went wrong.

1100
01:30:45,550 --> 01:30:49,053
I just didn’t let her out,
that’s all.

1101
01:30:51,150 --> 01:30:52,619
Isn't that the same thing?

1102
01:30:52,620 --> 01:30:53,769
It's different.

1103
01:30:54,416 --> 01:30:56,556
Locking someone up is a crime.

1104
01:31:03,860 --> 01:31:04,860
Letting her out

1105
01:31:06,000 --> 01:31:07,206
it's just being kind.

1106
01:31:08,290 --> 01:31:10,719
I don't have any kindness
left for her now.

1107
01:31:16,086 --> 01:31:17,540
She’s a bad person.

1108
01:31:18,620 --> 01:31:20,810
Someone who uses people

1109
01:31:21,090 --> 01:31:22,186
and dumps them.

1110
01:31:24,640 --> 01:31:25,939
So what are you going to do?

1111
01:31:26,870 --> 01:31:28,119
Just leave her like that?

1112
01:31:28,120 --> 01:31:29,632
What if she dies from hunger?

1113
01:31:29,860 --> 01:31:31,050
Isn't that interesting?

1114
01:31:31,890 --> 01:31:33,183
There must be no food left.

1115
01:31:35,950 --> 01:31:36,950
Mi-joo.

1116
01:31:37,450 --> 01:31:39,266
Isn’t this basically murder?

1117
01:31:40,310 --> 01:31:41,733
This is murder.

1118
01:31:42,350 --> 01:31:43,930
Then what do you want me to do?

1119
01:31:45,056 --> 01:31:46,590
So now, after everything…
simply let her out?

1120
01:31:46,670 --> 01:31:48,763
And say sorry &
I was just kidding.

1121
01:31:48,788 --> 01:31:49,630
Is that what you mean?

1122
01:31:50,030 --> 01:31:52,543
And she’ll just say,
'I was wrong too',

1123
01:31:52,880 --> 01:31:54,096
And that's it?

1124
01:31:54,330 --> 01:31:55,925
But still, this isn’t right.

1125
01:31:55,950 --> 01:31:57,316
You know what she's like.

1126
01:31:57,650 --> 01:31:59,040
Not just me.

1127
01:31:59,663 --> 01:32:02,250
She's gonna make us both accomplices
and put us in jail together.

1128
01:32:03,996 --> 01:32:06,443
Isn't that why you came to me?

1129
01:32:06,990 --> 01:32:08,710
Because you're scared?

1130
01:32:09,180 --> 01:32:10,699
Or else,

1131
01:32:10,700 --> 01:32:14,186
you would have already called the police
and construction workers to get her out.

1132
01:32:14,846 --> 01:32:15,975
Then what are you going to do?

1133
01:32:16,000 --> 01:32:17,973
Just leave her like that…
until she dies?

1134
01:32:28,765 --> 01:32:30,052
I don’t really know either.

1135
01:32:31,250 --> 01:32:35,265
Now that you know about it,
I feel relieved.

1136
01:32:36,250 --> 01:32:37,676
You make the decision.

1137
01:32:38,210 --> 01:32:39,256
I'll follow it,

1138
01:32:39,883 --> 01:32:40,983
no matter what.

1139
01:33:01,528 --> 01:33:03,754
You definitely won’t forgive me.

1140
01:33:09,400 --> 01:33:13,190
I struggled so much
to get this far… damn it.

1141
01:33:19,163 --> 01:33:21,723
The moment you get out,
you’ll destroy me completely, won’t you?

1142
01:33:25,950 --> 01:33:28,616
You’ll destroy me so badly that
no one will even find a trace, right?

1143
01:33:31,760 --> 01:33:32,793
I guess so.

1144
01:33:34,686 --> 01:33:36,646
Well, that’s just how you are.

1145
01:33:38,490 --> 01:33:39,660
Right.

1146
01:33:42,373 --> 01:33:43,953
Shit...

1147
01:33:48,698 --> 01:33:49,905
But Su-yeon...

1148
01:33:50,710 --> 01:33:52,300
You lied to me too.

1149
01:33:53,611 --> 01:33:55,025
You like women.

1150
01:33:57,610 --> 01:33:58,610
Don't you?

1151
01:34:46,040 --> 01:34:48,113
Bravo, well done!

1152
01:34:49,020 --> 01:34:51,960
Wow, today's final
rehearsal was amazing!

1153
01:34:52,600 --> 01:34:54,180
We still need to
fine-tune it a bit more.

1154
01:34:54,286 --> 01:34:55,513
Sit down, sit down.

1155
01:34:58,093 --> 01:35:00,693
I really enjoyed it.

1156
01:35:02,370 --> 01:35:06,250
I totally thought today was
the actual performance.

1157
01:35:06,970 --> 01:35:09,116
But why do you look so gloomy?

1158
01:35:10,000 --> 01:35:11,000
Me?

1159
01:35:13,410 --> 01:35:17,010
Are you hiding something from me?

1160
01:35:18,200 --> 01:35:19,526
Nothing like that.

1161
01:35:25,530 --> 01:35:28,380
Have you heard anything about Su-yeon?

1162
01:35:31,730 --> 01:35:32,936
No.

1163
01:35:37,400 --> 01:35:39,553
I thought we are finally
on the same team,

1164
01:35:39,578 --> 01:35:40,879
but now I doubt it.

1165
01:35:41,580 --> 01:35:42,580
Su-yeon,

1166
01:35:44,070 --> 01:35:45,980
she left saying she doesn't like you.

1167
01:35:46,770 --> 01:35:48,870
So, as her mom, if I keep hiring you...

1168
01:35:49,620 --> 01:35:52,223
No, if I keep appointing you,

1169
01:35:52,400 --> 01:35:55,240
I suddenly had this thought that
it would be hard for her to come back.

1170
01:35:55,910 --> 01:35:57,080
It really was sudden.

1171
01:35:59,050 --> 01:36:01,760
If Su-yeon keeps staying away like this,

1172
01:36:02,610 --> 01:36:05,096
what am I supposed to do
with our relationship?

1173
01:36:05,420 --> 01:36:06,510
I’m worried.

1174
01:36:09,400 --> 01:36:10,400
Right?

1175
01:36:13,260 --> 01:36:15,220
Ah, today was going so well..

1176
01:36:35,230 --> 01:36:38,740
<i>Su-yeon(2)</i>

1177
01:36:40,740 --> 01:36:43,870
<i>Su-yeon: it's me.</i>

1178
01:36:51,370 --> 01:36:53,603
<i>SHE(Su-yeon):  Have you guys been getting
along well while I wasn't around?</i>

1179
01:37:02,546 --> 01:37:04,034
What are you going to do?

1180
01:37:04,059 --> 01:37:06,286
Mi-joo, cheer up.

1181
01:37:06,765 --> 01:37:09,912
If she's gone, that means she's alive.
So we haven’t committed any serious crime,

1182
01:37:09,937 --> 01:37:10,745
right?

1183
01:37:10,939 --> 01:37:12,639
That's right,

1184
01:37:13,420 --> 01:37:14,445
But...

1185
01:37:14,700 --> 01:37:16,300
I've committed a great crime.

1186
01:37:16,740 --> 01:37:18,980
But it's better than murder, right?

1187
01:37:24,420 --> 01:37:26,140
I checked,

1188
01:37:27,480 --> 01:37:29,733
and the key is still
inside my bag as it is.

1189
01:37:31,000 --> 01:37:33,253
To be honest, I doubted you.

1190
01:37:34,340 --> 01:37:35,353
Me?

1191
01:37:35,860 --> 01:37:36,860
Yeah.

1192
01:37:39,230 --> 01:37:40,230
I mean,

1193
01:37:41,240 --> 01:37:42,500
let's just

1194
01:37:44,190 --> 01:37:45,469
wait and see.

1195
01:37:46,080 --> 01:37:48,293
That's not an easy place to get out.

1196
01:37:50,853 --> 01:37:52,273
We're staying calm, right?

1197
01:37:52,300 --> 01:37:53,453
No.

1198
01:37:54,120 --> 01:37:55,320
Go open it now.

1199
01:37:58,040 --> 01:37:59,546
Or I'll call the police.

1200
01:38:11,220 --> 01:38:14,089
The conductor suddenly had an emergency

1201
01:38:14,090 --> 01:38:15,820
and had to cancel the afternoon rehearsal.

1202
01:38:16,630 --> 01:38:17,814
And manager,

1203
01:38:18,630 --> 01:38:20,249
cellist Kim Mi-joo,

1204
01:38:20,250 --> 01:38:22,976
went to the hospital because
she was not feeling well.

1205
01:38:23,430 --> 01:38:24,563
That's all.

1206
01:38:26,410 --> 01:38:27,510
You can go.

1207
01:38:31,130 --> 01:38:32,590
This is scary.

1208
01:38:33,240 --> 01:38:34,663
Director, what is this?

1209
01:38:35,470 --> 01:38:36,543
After reading the text,

1210
01:38:36,940 --> 01:38:39,460
If someone is innocent,
they’ll rush into this room.

1211
01:38:39,485 --> 01:38:41,096
Or leave early if they’re guilty.

1212
01:38:41,620 --> 01:38:43,130
Wow.

1213
01:38:43,790 --> 01:38:45,639
So an agent can activate
the same phone number again

1214
01:38:45,640 --> 01:38:47,399
with just a copy of their ID card.

1215
01:38:47,400 --> 01:38:49,870
They probably never even thought of this

1216
01:38:50,240 --> 01:38:52,150
that you can activate the
same number again.

1217
01:38:53,380 --> 01:38:54,883
They’re totally panicked.

1218
01:38:58,120 --> 01:39:00,580
I... I’m so scared.

1219
01:39:02,300 --> 01:39:03,986
What have they done?

1220
01:39:04,546 --> 01:39:06,119
I'm really scared.

1221
01:39:07,920 --> 01:39:09,346
Is this the entrance?

1222
01:39:12,880 --> 01:39:14,866
It was behind this?

1223
01:39:16,373 --> 01:39:17,766
How do you open this?

1224
01:39:19,966 --> 01:39:20,973
Sung-jin.

1225
01:39:22,140 --> 01:39:23,620
There's no going back
if we do this.

1226
01:39:25,540 --> 01:39:27,128
How do I open this ?

1227
01:39:27,153 --> 01:39:29,145
I'm telling you,
there's no way out of here after this.

1228
01:39:29,170 --> 01:39:30,346
Mi-joo.

1229
01:40:58,270 --> 01:40:59,436
Su-yeon.

1230
01:41:01,830 --> 01:41:03,176
Su-yeon, are you okay?

1231
01:41:04,740 --> 01:41:05,870
See?

1232
01:41:07,130 --> 01:41:09,150
I told you she can't
get out of here easily.

1233
01:41:11,820 --> 01:41:13,806
Then what the hell was that text message?

1234
01:41:20,613 --> 01:41:21,613
Su-yeon.

1235
01:41:26,740 --> 01:41:27,840
Are you alright?

1236
01:41:30,760 --> 01:41:31,853
She's still alive.

1237
01:41:35,420 --> 01:41:36,566
Su-yeon.

1238
01:41:39,570 --> 01:41:41,260
Wake up.

1239
01:41:44,680 --> 01:41:45,680
Su-yeon.

1240
01:41:45,730 --> 01:41:46,796
Su-yeon, enough.

1241
01:41:47,160 --> 01:41:49,323
Suyeon, stop it.

1242
01:41:51,260 --> 01:41:52,355
She's out of her mind.

1243
01:41:52,380 --> 01:41:53,070
She's crazy.

1244
01:41:53,170 --> 01:41:54,730
- Let go!
- Let's get out of here.

1245
01:41:55,010 --> 01:41:55,875
- She's crazy.
- I'm telling you to come out.

1246
01:41:55,900 --> 01:41:57,129
Sung-jin, let's get out of here quickly!

1247
01:41:57,130 --> 01:41:58,800
- Let go of me!
- She's crazy.

1248
01:41:59,250 --> 01:42:00,850
- Let's get out of here.
- Let go!

1249
01:42:01,346 --> 01:42:02,346
Just let go of me!

1250
01:42:06,570 --> 01:42:07,643
Su-yeon.

1251
01:42:17,330 --> 01:42:18,336
Get up.

1252
01:42:19,850 --> 01:42:20,910
Are you okay?

1253
01:42:22,590 --> 01:42:23,843
Let's go out, Sung-jin.

1254
01:42:24,210 --> 01:42:25,616
- Let's go.
- I can handle it myself.

1255
01:42:47,670 --> 01:42:49,910
Wash up and eat something.

1256
01:42:51,060 --> 01:42:52,346
I'm going to the police station.

1257
01:42:53,020 --> 01:42:54,123
No.

1258
01:42:57,880 --> 01:42:59,100
I said no!

1259
01:43:01,330 --> 01:43:02,456
I'm hungry.

1260
01:43:03,710 --> 01:43:04,710
Order me something.

1261
01:43:06,040 --> 01:43:07,040
Kimchi stew.

1262
01:43:16,500 --> 01:43:17,500
Okay.

1263
01:43:22,170 --> 01:43:24,013
I'll take a shower first.

1264
01:43:25,750 --> 01:43:27,440
I really wanted to shower.

1265
01:43:35,730 --> 01:43:36,969
Help me take it off.

1266
01:44:06,970 --> 01:44:08,014
Mi-joo.

1267
01:44:10,490 --> 01:44:12,389
You're standing right
in front of the mirror, right?

1268
01:44:18,080 --> 01:44:19,453
I'm going to take a shower now,

1269
01:44:19,610 --> 01:44:20,713
in hot water.

1270
01:44:25,890 --> 01:44:26,890
Hey.

1271
01:44:27,290 --> 01:44:29,130
If you do something stupid like me,

1272
01:44:29,510 --> 01:44:30,596
You know, right?

1273
01:44:31,050 --> 01:44:32,303
I won’t give you any water.

1274
01:44:36,460 --> 01:44:37,576
Let's talk about the rest,

1275
01:44:38,060 --> 01:44:40,280
after I take a shower, Mi-joo.

1276
01:44:57,560 --> 01:45:00,414
I was worried since you
didn’t contact me at all.

1277
01:45:00,440 --> 01:45:03,127
I didn’t expect you to show up like this
and pay the balance as well.

1278
01:45:03,152 --> 01:45:04,974
Of course, it's Shin Su-yeon.

1279
01:45:05,490 --> 01:45:07,312
How's Mi-joo?

1280
01:45:07,860 --> 01:45:09,023
Teacher

1281
01:45:09,520 --> 01:45:10,836
You know everything, right?

1282
01:45:11,060 --> 01:45:12,410
About you two?

1283
01:45:12,800 --> 01:45:15,683
Hey! I’m your teacher!

1284
01:45:16,626 --> 01:45:18,020
Now that I'm getting married…

1285
01:45:18,260 --> 01:45:20,266
things got a bit awkward between us.

1286
01:45:20,750 --> 01:45:21,750
Still,

1287
01:45:22,170 --> 01:45:24,416
I want to keep our bond from breaking.

1288
01:45:25,500 --> 01:45:28,130
We shouldn’t lose people, you know?

1289
01:45:29,730 --> 01:45:32,676
I used to look at you and think,

1290
01:45:34,010 --> 01:45:36,250
“No one can match your possessiveness."

1291
01:45:37,150 --> 01:45:38,930
In the end, you get everything, huh?

1292
01:45:39,840 --> 01:45:41,602
Even my house is yours now.

1293
01:45:42,400 --> 01:45:44,473
Now that I hear you say it,
I guess you're right.

1294
01:45:58,570 --> 01:45:59,570
But, teacher...

1295
01:46:02,540 --> 01:46:03,616
by any chance...

1296
01:46:04,520 --> 01:46:07,013
did you say something
bad about me to Mi-joo?

1297
01:46:08,170 --> 01:46:10,130
That I just use people
and throw them away.

1298
01:46:13,870 --> 01:46:15,576
I used to like you, teacher.

1299
01:46:26,280 --> 01:46:28,160
Wow, the flowers are so nice.

1300
01:46:29,690 --> 01:46:30,746
And teacher,

1301
01:46:31,110 --> 01:46:33,893
your house is so good.

1302
01:46:34,826 --> 01:46:36,286
I'm so happy!

1303
01:46:36,680 --> 01:46:37,853
Really,

1304
01:46:38,730 --> 01:46:40,636
It's a house that brings happiness.

1305
01:47:27,790 --> 01:47:28,916
Going golfing?

1306
01:47:30,556 --> 01:47:32,420
Oh, did I wake you up?

1307
01:47:32,730 --> 01:47:33,730
No.

1308
01:47:34,590 --> 01:47:35,756
I was just about to get up.

1309
01:47:37,730 --> 01:47:40,090
You’re really into golf these days.

1310
01:47:41,690 --> 01:47:42,690
Yeah. It’s fun.

1311
01:47:44,130 --> 01:47:45,130
Mom,

1312
01:47:46,240 --> 01:47:48,160
said we should go out together
next week.

1313
01:47:48,800 --> 01:47:49,800
Yeah, I heard.

1314
01:47:51,210 --> 01:47:52,003
Sleep a bit more.

1315
01:47:52,190 --> 01:47:53,230
I'll be back.

1316
01:47:53,760 --> 01:47:54,760
Have a great game!

1317
01:48:42,063 --> 01:48:43,090
Did you lock it well?

1318
01:48:56,573 --> 01:48:57,600
Toss me the key.

1319
01:49:37,650 --> 01:49:38,936
You really dressed up nicely.

1320
01:49:52,566 --> 01:49:53,660
Were you waiting for me?

1321
01:49:55,110 --> 01:49:56,110
Yeah.

1322
01:50:07,690 --> 01:50:08,690
Take it off.

1323
01:50:40,490 --> 01:50:47,830
[HIDDEN FACE]

